From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: gahingwoo <huhuvmb88@outlook.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +1200
Subject: [PATCH 27/27] DEBUG: rocket prep_bo explicit dcache-invalidate probe

The prep_bo dual-path cache check used memremap(MEMREMAP_WC), which returns
NULL on RAM (wc=0xdeadbeef is just the NULL marker), so it never actually
cross-checked the CPU cache against DRAM. Add an explicit dcache_inval_poc() +
re-read: if the forced value differs from the dma_sync'd read, the "empty
output" was a stale-cache READ artifact (the DPU did write DRAM). Result on
RK3576: they match (output truly unwritten) -> the wall is real, not a
cache-read artifact.
Signed-off-by: Jiaxing Hu <huhuvmb88@outlook.com>
---
diff --git a/drivers/accel/rocket/rocket_gem.c b/drivers/accel/rocket/rocket_gem.c
--- a/drivers/accel/rocket/rocket_gem.c
+++ b/drivers/accel/rocket/rocket_gem.c
@@ -11,6 +11,7 @@
 #include <linux/iosys-map.h>
 
 #include <linux/moduleparam.h>
+#include <asm/cacheflush.h>	/* Kiln: dcache_inval_poc for the prep_bo cache probe */
 
 #include "rocket_drv.h"
 #include "rocket_gem.h"
@@ -214,6 +215,24 @@
 
 		if (wc)
 			memunmap((void *)wc);
+
+		/*
+		 * Kiln: the memremap-WC uncached cross-check fails on RAM (NULL ->
+		 * wc=0xdeadbeef), so the "cached" read above only reflects DRAM IF
+		 * dma_sync_sgtable_for_cpu() actually invalidated. The NPU is
+		 * non-coherent and the vendor uses an explicit dcache_inval_poc, not
+		 * dma_sync. Force an explicit invalidate-to-PoC of the first line and
+		 * re-read: if this DIFFERS from "cached", dma_sync did NOT invalidate
+		 * -> the DPU wrote real output that we were reading stale (the "empty"
+		 * wall is a cache-read artifact). If it matches, the DPU truly wrote
+		 * nothing.
+		 */
+		dcache_inval_poc((unsigned long)cached,
+				 (unsigned long)cached + 16);
+		drm_info(dev,
+			 "rocket dbg prep_bo INVAL: iova=0x%llx forced=%08x %08x %08x %08x\n",
+			 (unsigned long long)rkt_obj->mm.start,
+			 cached[0], cached[1], cached[2], cached[3]);
 	}
 
 	drm_gem_object_put(gem_obj);
